2^4\equiv1\pmod 5\implies 2^{1990}=2^2\cdot(2^4)^{997}\equiv4\cdot1^{997}\pmod 5\equiv4\ \ \ \ (1)
2^{198}\equiv1\pmod {199}\implies 2^{1990}=2^{10}\cdot(2^{198})^{10}\equiv1024\cdot1^{10}\pmod{199}\equiv 29\ \ \ \ (2)
2^{1990}\equiv0\pmod2\ \ \ \ (3)
